The police say three people have been arrested in connection with the kidnapping of an 11-year-old-girl. eNCA senior reporter Barry Bateman spoke with Thulasizwe Simelane about the progress in the case. Courtesy of #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Three people have been arrested for the abduction of an 11-year-old girl in November. The Crime Intelligence Kidnapping Task Team, supported by the Joburg Flying Squad, rescued the child in Soweto on Wednesday. READ: Girl (11) reunited with family after kidnapping ordeal She was held captive for 48 days after being snatched by gunmen outside her primary school in Mayfair. The child's father has thanked the public for the outpouring of support. The Gauteng Education Department said they will provide all the necessary support to the girl and her family.